  "text": "Consistency. The structure (1.1), where µ 0 is Gaussian, arises in the application of the Bayesian methodology to the solution of inverse problems. In that context it is interesting to study posterior consistency: the idea that the posterior concentrates near the truth which gave rise to the data, in the small noise or large sample size limits; these two limits are intimately related and indeed there are theorems that quantify this connection for certain linear inverse problems [CITATION_1] .",
